
<api_design_task>
Design a complete REST API for [your feature/product]
</api_design_task>

<business_requirements>
<core_functionality>
[What does this API need to do? Be specific about user actions]
</core_functionality>

<data_relationships>
[How do your entities relate? Users → Posts → Comments, etc.]
</data_relationships>

<scale_expectations>
- Expected requests per second: [number]
- Data volume: [amount]
- Geographic distribution: [regions]
</scale_expectations>
</business_requirements>

<design_constraints>
- Must be RESTful (no shortcuts)
- Authentication: [JWT/OAuth/etc.]
- Rate limiting: [requirements]
- Versioning strategy: [URL/header/etc.]
</design_constraints>

<deliverables>
1. Complete endpoint list with HTTP methods
2. Request/response schemas in JSON
3. Error handling patterns with status codes
4. Authentication flow diagram
5. Rate limiting strategy
6. Database schema recommendations
7. Caching strategy for read-heavy endpoints
</deliverables>

<success_criteria>
The API should be intuitive enough that a frontend dev can use it without asking questions.
</success_criteria>
</api_design_task>